		"creator" : "Michael Olson",
		"description" : "<p>Yesterday at the <a href=%34http%3a%2f%2fwww.cloudidentitysummit.com%2f%34 target=%34_blank%34>Cloud Identity Summit<%2fa> in Denver, Colorado, Lee Hammond from <a href=%34http%3a%2f%2fwww.interscope.com%34 target=%34_blank%34>Interscope Geffen A%38amp;M Records<%2fa> (a division of Universal Music Group), and Brian Kissel, CEO of <a href=%34http%3a%2f%2fwww.janrain.com%34>Janrain<%2fa>, spoke jointly about the use of social media tools to improve customer acquisition and retainment. Hammond shared Interscope%38#39;s experience to achieve these goals, beginning with a native OpenID implementation and resulting in a relationship with <a href=%34http%3a%2f%2fwww.janrain.com%34>Janrain<%2fa>.<%2fp>				
											<p>Beginning in 2007, Interscope Records began accepting AOL identities for login on its 125 music artist websites through an in-house implementation of OpenID. Below is a screenshot of Interscope%38#39;s third-party login system on Eve.com in 2007%3a<%2fp>				
											<p><img alt=%34Eve.com's old login process%34 src=%34%2fsites%2fdefault%2ffiles%2finterscope-1_1.JPG%34 style=%34width%3a 550px; height%3a 293px;%34 %2f><%2fp>				
											<p>	And on another site%3a<%2fp>				
											<p><img alt=%34rooney%34 src=%34%2fsites%2fdefault%2ffiles%2finterscope-2_0.JPG%34 style=%34width%3a 550px; height%3a 351px;%34 %2f><%2fp>				
											<p>	By 2008, with additional social networks (such as Facebook, Google and MySpace) becoming available for login, Interscope sought to leverage the new identity providers, make the user experience more intuitive, and minimize the challenge of scaling and maintaining the system.<%2fp>				
											<p>Interscope turned to <a href=%34%2fproducts%2fengage%34>Janrain Engage<%2fa> in late 2008. Choosing Janrain has enabled Interscope to <strong>instantly leverage additional social networks<%2fstrong> (such as Twitter and Windows Live) as they become available and outsource maintenance of the disparate APIs from each network.<%2fp>				
											<p>The result? <strong>55% of all logins across 125 music artist sites occur through <a href=%34%2fproducts%2fengage%34>Janrain Engage<%2fa><%2fstrong>, with that percentage as high as <a href=%34http%3a%2f%2fwww.readwriteweb.com%2fcloud%2f2010%2f02%2flady-gaga-facebook-login-twitter.php%34 target=%34_blank%34><strong>89% on sites like LadyGaga.com<%2fstrong><%2fa>. Overall <strong>registration rates on all artist sites have improved by 10%<%2fstrong>, in part due to the intuitive user interface provided by <a href=%34%2fproducts%2fengage%34>Janrain Engage<%2fa>%3a<%2fp>				
											<p><img alt=%34lady gaga%34 src=%34%2fsites%2fdefault%2ffiles%2finterscope-3_0.JPG%34 style=%34width%3a 550px; height%3a 435px;%34 %2f><%2fp>				
											<p>%38nbsp;<%2fp>				
											<p>Here are slides from the presentation at Cloud Identity Summit%3a<%2fp>				
											<div id=%34__ss_4817856%34 style=%34width%3a 425px;%34><strong style=%34margin%3a 12px 0pt 4px; display%3a block;%34><a href=%34http%3a%2f%2fwww.slideshare.net%2flhannah%2fjanrain-and-interscope-records-cloud-identity-summit-presentation-july-2010%34 title=%34Janrain and Interscope Records Cloud Identity Summit presentation July 2010%34>Janrain and Interscope Records Cloud Identity Summit presentation July 2010<%2fa><%2fstrong>				
