		"title" : "Tribune Interactive Gets Creative with Beautiful Babies Contest",
		"link" : "http://www.janrain.comblogs/tribune-interactive-gets-creative-beautiful-babies-contest",
		"creator" : "Michael Olson",
		"description" : "<p><a href=%34http%3a%2f%2fwww.tribuneinteractive.com%2f%34>Tribune Interactive<%2fa> recently began a <a href=%34http%3a%2f%2ftribunepromotions.com%2fbabies%2f%34 target=%34_blank%34>contest to uncover the most beautiful baby<%2fa> in the U.S.%38nbsp; The Tribune is fostering wide participation by allowing visitors to media websites in local markets (such as <a href=%34http%3a%2f%2fwww.chicagotribune.com%2f%34 target=%34_blank%34>The Chicago Tribune<%2fa>, <a href=%34http%3a%2f%2fwww.latimes.com%2f%34 target=%34_blank%34>LA Times<%2fa>, <a href=%34http%3a%2f%2fwww.baltimoresun.com%2f%34 target=%34_blank%34>Baltimore Sun<%2fa>, and <a href=%34http%3a%2f%2fwww.orlandosentinel.com%2f%34 target=%34_blank%34>Orlando Sentinel<%2fa>) to register on the site and vote for their favorite babies.%38nbsp; The parents of the most chic child, as voted upon by fans across the U.S. until the end of July, will win $5,000.<%2fp>				
											<p>The company is facilitating fan engagement by leveraging the social network and email accounts of its visitors during the sign up process, in this case through the implementation of <a href=%34%2f..%2f..%2fproducts%2fengage%34>Janrain Enage<%2fa>.<%2fp>				
											<p style=%34text-align%3a center;%34><img alt=%34%34 src=%34%2fsites%2fdefault%2ffiles%2fchicago-tribune-2.JPG%34 style=%34width%3a 550px; height%3a 428px;%34 %2f><%2fp>				
											<p>Tribune Interactive%38#39;s promotion is another example of how removing barriers to registration can yield sharp improvements in customer engagement.%38nbsp; In late 2008, rock band AFI <a href=%34%2f..%2f..%2fblogs%2fopenid-case-study-afi-begin-transmission-project%34>launched a contest<%2fa> to allow users to submit and vote for fan-generated audition videos, with the winner invited to perform on the band%38#39;s then upcoming album.%38nbsp; The contest drew great interest from the band%38#39;s fanbase, and by leveraging <a href=%34%2fproducts%2fengage%34>Janrain Engage<%2fa>, AFI made it easy for fans to sign up on the site, submit videos and vote for their favorite fan auditions.<%2fp>				
											<p>Tribune Interactive has encouraged broad participation by removing the registration hassle and enabling visitors to sign up on the site with an existing social network or email account.%38nbsp; We will stay tuned to see who America crowns as its most beautiful baby.<%2fp>",
